First, gather our old comrades.

13
00:03:13,427 --> 00:03:15,387
Send them a sign.

14
00:03:27,374 --> 00:03:30,444
Nagini tells me
the old Muggle caretaker...

15
00:03:31,044 --> 00:03:34,294
...is standing just outside the door.

16
00:03:34,915 --> 00:03:39,575
Step aside, Wormtail,
so I can give our guest a proper greeting.

17
00:03:40,387 --> 00:03:41,997
Avada Kedavra!l

18
00:03:47,260 --> 00:03:48,570
Harry.

19
00:03:49,496 --> 00:03:50,956
Harry!

20
00:03:52,466 --> 00:03:54,046
Are you all right?

21
00:03:54,968 --> 00:03:56,808
Hermione. Bad dream.

22
00:03:57,237 --> 00:04:00,197
-When did you get here?
-Just now. You?

23
00:04:00,774 --> 00:04:01,854
Last night.

24
00:04:02,175 --> 00:04:04,135
Wake up! Wake up, Ronald!

25
00:04:04,578 --> 00:04:05,688
Bloody hell.

26
00:04:06,012 --> 00:04:07,352
Honestly, get dressed.

27
00:04:08,281 --> 00:04:09,801
And don't go back to sleep.

28
00:04:10,183 --> 00:04:13,113
Come on, Ron!
Your mother says breakfast’s ready!

29
00:04:20,192 --> 00:04:22,683
-Ron, where are we actually going?
-Don’t know.

30
00:04:23,497 --> 00:04:26,367
-Hey, Dad. Where are we going?
-Haven't the foggiest.

31
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:28,272
Keep up!

32
00:04:31,037 --> 00:04:32,647
Arthur!

33
00:04:33,039 --> 00:04:34,789
It’s about time, son.

34
00:04:35,208 --> 00:04:39,048
Sorry, Amos. Some of us
had a bit of a sleepy start.

35
00:04:39,746 --> 00:04:44,726
This is Amos Diggory, everyone.
Works with me at the Ministry.

36
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:47,809
And this strapping young lad
must be Cedric, am I right?

37
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:49,308
Yes, sir.

38
00:04:49,623 --> 00:04:51,082
This way.

39
00:04:53,026 --> 00:04:55,986
Merlin’s beard!
You must be Harry Potter.

40
00:04:56,563 --> 00:04:58,962
-Yes, sir.
-Great, great pleasure.

41
00:04:59,466 --> 00:05:01,046
Pleasure to meet you too, sir.

42
00:05:03,904 --> 00:05:06,244
Yes, it’s just over there.

43
00:05:08,842 --> 00:05:10,421
-Shall we?
-Oh, yeah.

44
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:11,861
We don't want to be late.

45
00:05:12,179 --> 00:05:15,808
Come on. Nearly there now.
Get yourself into a good position.

46
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:19,367
Why are they all standing around
that manky old boot?

47
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:22,010
-That isn't just any manky old boot.
-It's a Portkey.

48
00:05:22,489 --> 00:05:23,688
Time to go!

49
00:05:24,024 --> 00:05:25,424
What's a Portkey?

50
00:05:25,792 --> 00:05:29,332
-Ready! After three. One, two...
-Harry!

51
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:30,955
...three!

52
00:05:42,142 --> 00:05:43,132
Let go, kids!

53
00:05:43,443 --> 00:05:45,722
-What?!
-Let go!

54
00:05:58,091 --> 00:06:00,341
V'll bet that cleared your sinuses, eh?

55
00:06:01,728 --> 00:06:03,898
-Total shambles, as per usual.
-Thanks.

56
00:06:10,003 --> 00:06:11,873
Go on, look at that!

57
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:16,352
Well, kids, welcome to
the Quidditch World Cup!

58
00:06:19,913 --> 00:06:22,223
Stay together! Keep up, girls!

59
00:06:24,084 --> 00:06:25,194
Look!

60
00:06:26,253 --> 00:06:28,243
Come on! Keep up, girls!

61
