67
00:06:52,279 --> 00:06:53,619
What?

68
00:07:01,221 --> 00:07:02,891
-Excellent, excellent.
-Ginny, look!

69
00:07:03,290 --> 00:07:04,430
-All to the bath.
-Look.

70
00:07:04,758 --> 00:07:06,948
Girls, choose a bunk and unpack.

71
00:07:07,861 --> 00:07:10,001
Ron, get out of the kitchen.
We're all hungry.

72
00:07:10,463 --> 00:07:12,633
-Yeah, get out of the kitchen, Ron!
-Feet off the table!

73
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:15,089
-Feet off the table!
-Feet off the table!

74
00:07:16,603 --> 00:07:18,533
Il love magic.

75
00:07:34,054 --> 00:07:37,123
Get your Quidditch World Cup
programs here!

76
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:40,570
Blimey, Dad. How far up are we?

77
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:42,387
Well, put it this way:

78
00:07:42,796 --> 00:07:44,316
If it rains...

79
00:07:44,698 --> 00:07:46,777
..-you'll be the first to know.

80
00:07:47,801 --> 00:07:49,911
Father and I are in
the minister's box...

81
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:53,240
...by personal invitation
of Cornelius Fudge himself.

82
00:07:53,807 --> 00:07:55,737
Don’t boast, Draco.

83
00:07:56,176 --> 00:07:58,015
There’s no need with these people.

84
00:08:00,747 --> 00:08:02,967
Do enjoy yourself, won't you?

85
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:05,260
While you can.

86
00:08:18,898 --> 00:08:22,998
Come on up. Take your seats. I told you
these seats would be worth waiting for.

87
00:08:23,737 --> 00:08:25,377
Come on!

88
00:08:27,841 --> 00:08:29,571
