There are too many people.

1385
02:10:54,980 --> 02:10:56,469
Let me through.

1386
02:10:56,849 --> 02:10:58,189
Let me through!

1387
02:11:00,286 --> 02:11:01,396
Let me through!

1388
02:11:01,721 --> 02:11:02,950
That's my son!

1389
02:11:04,423 --> 02:11:05,683
That's my boy!

1390
02:11:08,694 --> 02:11:11,094
It's my boy!

1391
02:11:14,233 --> 02:11:17,363
-Come on. Get up. Easy, easy!
-No.

1392
02:11:17,970 --> 02:11:20,580
This is not where you want to be
right now. Come on.

1393
02:11:21,607 --> 02:11:23,537
No!

1394
02:11:26,879 --> 02:11:28,989
It’s all right, I got you.

1395
02:11:29,448 --> 02:11:32,378
I got you. Come on. Easy, now.

1396
02:11:36,789 --> 02:11:38,369
No!

1397
02:11:39,692 --> 02:11:41,332
No!

1398
02:12:23,969 --> 02:12:25,459
Are you all right, Potter?

1399
02:12:26,238 --> 02:12:27,938
Does it hurt? That?

1400
02:12:28,340 --> 02:12:29,920
Not so much now.

1401
02:12:31,076 --> 02:12:32,916
Perhaps I'd better take a look at it.

1402
02:12:36,315 --> 02:12:38,065
The cup was a Portkey.

1403
02:12:41,020 --> 02:12:42,630
Someone had bewitched it.

1404
02:12:43,122 --> 02:12:44,962
What was it like?

1405
02:12:45,558 --> 02:12:47,018
-What was he like?
-Who?

1406
02:12:47,393 --> 02:12:48,943
The Dark Lord.

1407
02:12:51,464 --> 02:12:54,184
What was it like
to stand in his presence?

1408
02:12:55,835 --> 02:12:57,415
I don’t know.

1409
02:13:00,473 --> 02:13:03,053
It was like I'd fallen
into one of my dreams...

1410
02:13:06,378 --> 02:13:08,128
.. into one of my nightmares.

1411
02:13:27,099 --> 02:13:28,469
Were there others?

1412
02:13:28,834 --> 02:13:30,824
In the graveyard, were there others?

1413
02:13:35,040 --> 02:13:36,269
he.

1414
02:13:37,142 --> 02:13:40,602
I don’t think I said anything
about a graveyard, professor.

1415
02:13:48,521 --> 02:13:51,391
“Marvelous creatures, dragons,
aren't they?”

1416
02:13:56,195 --> 02:13:58,884
Did you think that miserable oaf
would've led you into the woods...

1417
02:13:59,431 --> 02:14:01,101
.. if [hadn't suggested it?

1418
02:14:04,870 --> 02:14:08,120
Do you think Cedric Diggory would’ ve
told you to open the egg underwater...

1419
02:14:08,741 --> 02:14:10,931
.if [hadn't told him first myself?

1420
02:14:12,845 --> 02:14:15,185
Did you think Neville Longbottom,
the witless wonder...

1421
02:14:15,681 --> 02:14:18,491
...could’ve provided you with gillyweed
if ! hadn't given him the book...

1422
02:14:19,051 --> 02:14:20,421
...that led him straight to it?

1423
02:14:29,028 --> 02:14:32,538
It was you from the beginning.
You put my name in the Goblet of Fire.

1424
02:14:33,599 --> 02:14:36,789
-You bewitched Krum, but you--
-"But-- But--"

1425
02:14:37,403 --> 02:14:39,303
You won because ! made it so, Potter.

1426
02:14:40,205 --> 02:14:43,275
You ended up in that graveyard tonight
because it was meant to be so.

1427
02:14:43,876 --> 02:14:45,016
And now the deed is done.

1428
02:14:46,845 --> 02:14:50,655
The blood that runs through these veins
runs within the Dark Lord.

1429
02:14:59,692 --> 02:15:02,762
Imagine how he will reward me
when he learns...

1430
02:15:04,129 --> 02:15:06,318
...that I have once and for all...

1431
02:15:07,232 --> 02:15:11,042
... silenced the great Harry Potter.

1432
02:15:11,737 --> 02:15:12,847
Expelliarmus!

1433
02:15:17,710 --> 02:15:18,820
Severus.

1434
02:15:21,447 --> 02:15:22,757
That’s it, take it.

1435
02:15:24,917 --> 02:15:27,957
-Do you know who I am?
-Albus Dumbledore.

1436
02:15:28,554 --> 02:15:30,924
-Are you Alastor Moody? Are you?
-No.

1437
02:15:31,423 --> 02:15:34,143
Is he in this room? Is he in this room?

1438
02:15:37,563 --> 02:15:38,903
Harry, away from there!

1439
02:16:00,085 --> 02:16:03,015
-You all right, Alastor?
-I'm sorry, Albus.

1440
02:16:04,390 --> 02:16:06,200
That’s Moody. But then who's--?

1441
02:16:08,260 --> 02:16:09,220
Polyjuice Potion.

1442
02:16:09,528 --> 02:16:12,368
Now we know who's been stealing
from your stores, Severus.

1443
02:16:12,998 --> 02:16:14,697
We'll get you up in a minute.

1444
02:16:49,368 --> 02:16:50,598
Harry!

1445
02:16:54,440 --> 02:16:56,370
Barty Crouch Junior.

1446
02:16:56,875 --> 02:16:59,455
I'll show you mine
if you show me yours.

1447
02:17:02,181 --> 02:17:03,231
Your arm, Harry.

1448
02:17:07,753 --> 02:17:09,713
You know what this means, don’t you?

1449
02:17:10,888 --> 02:17:12,058
He’s back.

1450
02:17:13,424 --> 02:17:15,295
Lord Voldemort has returned.

1451
02:17:16,495 --> 02:17:18,545
I'm sorry, sir. 1 couldn't help it.

1452
02:17:19,031 --> 02:17:23,011
Send an owl to Azkaban. I think
they'll find they’re missing a prisoner.

1453
02:17:24,036 --> 02:17:26,226
-l'll be welcomed back like a hero.
-Perhaps.

1454
02:17:27,106 --> 02:17:29,626
