for heroes.

1455
02:17:49,861 --> 02:17:52,201
Today, we acknowledge...

1456
02:17:53,232 --> 02:17:55,662
...a really terrible loss.

1457
02:17:58,102 --> 02:18:00,532
Cedric Diggory was, as you all know...

1458
02:18:01,039 --> 02:18:03,089
..exceptionally hard-working...

1459
02:18:04,276 --> 02:18:06,356
...infinitely fair-minded...

1460
02:18:07,212 --> 02:18:09,232
..and, most importantly...

1461
02:18:09,815 --> 02:18:13,825
...a fierce, fierce friend.

1462
02:18:15,521 --> 02:18:19,361
Now, I think, therefore, you have
the right to know exactly how he died.

1463
02:18:22,928 --> 02:18:24,268
You see...

1464
02:18:25,297 --> 02:18:27,137
...Cedric Diggory was murdered...

1465
02:18:28,299 --> 02:18:30,049
...by Lord Voldemort!

1466
02:18:32,204 --> 02:18:35,333
The Ministry of Magic
does not wish me to tell you this.

1467
02:18:36,407 --> 02:18:39,657
But not to do so, I think,
would be an insult to his memory.

1468
02:18:42,281 --> 02:18:43,741
Now, the pain...

1469
02:18:44,116 --> 02:18:47,335
..-we all feel at this dreadful loss
reminds me...

1470
02:18:47,952 --> 02:18:49,123
..and reminds us...

1471
02:18:49,454 --> 02:18:52,704
...that while we may come from different
places and speak in different tongues...

1472
02:18:53,325 --> 02:18:56,345
..-our hearts beat as one.

1473
02:18:57,262 --> 02:18:59,042
In light of recent events...

1474
02:18:59,630 --> 02:19:03,971
...the bonds of friendship we've made
this year will be more important than ever.

1475
02:19:05,437 --> 02:19:10,127
Remember that, and Cedric Diggory
will not have died in vain.

1476
02:19:11,209 --> 02:19:13,080
You remember that...

1477
02:19:13,946 --> 02:19:16,606
...-and we'll celebrate a boy who was...

1478
02:19:17,516 --> 02:19:19,686
..-kind and honest...

1479
02:19:20,485 --> 02:19:24,525
.and brave and true,
tight to the very end.

1480
02:19:50,315 --> 02:19:52,095
I never liked these curtains.

1481
02:19:52,951 --> 02:19:55,291
Set them on fire in my fourth year.

1482
02:19:55,954 --> 02:19:57,564
By accident, of course.

1483
02:20:03,462 --> 02:20:07,302
I put you in terrible danger
this year, Harry. I’m sorry.

1484
02:20:11,236 --> 02:20:12,726
Professor...

1485
02:20:13,138 --> 02:20:15,768
...when I was in the graveyard,
there was a moment...

1486
02:20:16,942 --> 02:20:20,812
..-when Voldemort’s wand and mine
sort of connected.

1487
02:20:22,915 --> 02:20:24,965
Priori Incantatem.

1488
02:20:29,388 --> 02:20:31,788
You saw your parents that night,
didn’t you?

1489
02:20:32,691 --> 02:20:34,301
They reappeared.

1490
02:20:35,994 --> 02:20:39,304
No spell can reawaken the dead, Harry.
Il trust you know that.

1491
02:20:42,334 --> 02:20:44,614
Dark and difficult times lie ahead.

1492
02:20:45,404 --> 02:20:49,654
Soon we must all face the choice
between what is right and what is easy.

1493
02:20:53,612 --> 02:20:55,071
But remember this:

1494
02:20:55,447 --> 02:20:57,147
You have friends here.

1495
02:20:59,384 --> 02:21:00,934
You're not alone.

1496
02:21:21,840 --> 02:21:23,360
Hermione.

1497
02:21:23,976 --> 02:21:25,726
This is for you.

1498
02:21:26,578 --> 02:21:28,508
Write to me. Promise.

1499
02:21:29,881 --> 02:21:31,110
Bye.

1500
02:21:37,522 --> 02:21:39,222
Au revoir, Ron.

1501
02:22:23,402 --> 02:22:25,622
Do you think we'll ever just have
a quiet year at Hogwarts?

1502
02:22:26,104 --> 02:22:27,094
-No.
-No.

1503
02:22:27,406 --> 02:22:31,246
No, I didn’t think so. Oh, well.
What’s life without a few dragons?

1504
02:22:36,181 --> 02:22:38,671
Everything's going to change now,
isn’t it?

1505
02:22:46,324 --> 02:22:47,614
Yes.

1506
02:22:52,531 --> 02:22:55,431
Promise you'll write this summer.
Both of you.

1507
02:22:56,001 --> 02:22:58,251
I won't. You know I won't.

1508
02:22:59,838 --> 02:23:03,148
-Harry will, won't you?
-Yeah. Every week.

1509
02:37:00,344 --> 02:37:02,094
[ENGLISH]

